The course is focussed on tha basics of statistical analysis and the statistical software R. It covers the basic concepts of statistical analysis, especially from the perspective of political science and the implementation of basic models in R. 
Kursuse tuumiku moodustavad arvutiklassis toimuvad praktikumid, milles koos kursuses osalejatega töötatakse läbi praktikumideks ette valmistatud materjalid. Praktikume täiendavad keskelt läbi iga kolme nädala tagant toimuvad (võimalusel online) loengud, milles tutvustatakse käsitletavate meetodite üldisemaid põhimõtteid.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objectives of the course are: - introducing the basic principles of statistical analysis in the social sciences; - introducing the basic methods of statistical analysis in the social sciences; - teaching the basics of using R for statistical analysis; - implementing the basic methods for the analysis of a specific research task.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course, the students have acquired the basic knowledge to do and to understand statistical analyses in the social sciences and are able to implement such analyses using R. They are familiar with the basic concepts and models in statistics, are able to evaluate and prepare data for analyses and choose statistical models accordingly. They are also able to interpret and present the results of their analyses and visualise their data.
